author: Inside Edition
description: The suspect in the murder of two Arizona teens posted videos of himself firing a homemade weapon. Thomas Brown's videos were on a YouTube channel he uses to promote his 3D printing business. Police say Brown shot and killed Evan Clark and Pandora Kjolsrud, who were on a Memorial Day camping trip to Mount Ord. Brown served in the Arizona National Guard for nine years, leaving in 2022 with the rank of Staff Sergeant.
title: Chilling Video Shows Double Murder Suspect Thomas Brown Firing Weapon

author: Inside Edition
description: Megastar Taylor Swift appeared on "The Tonight Show," and told Jimmy Fallon she was never "officially" offered the halftime show. She seemed to suggest that she won't do the halftime show until her fiance, Travis Kelce, retires from football. Meanwhile, President Trump is weighing in on the choice of Bad Bunny to perform at the Superbowl. The Trump administration says it's sending ICE agents to the big game.
title: Taylor Swift Sets The Record Straight About The Super Bowl

author: Inside Edition
description: Denise Richards testified in court that her ex, Aaron Phypers, "would often threaten to throw me through the windows and off balconies. He's almost killed me so many damn times." Phypers fired back, telling reporters, "It's a bunch of lies." Inside Edition sat down with Phypers in September, and now that interview may take center stage at a court hearing. Denise's lawyers are asking it to be introduced as evidence.
title: Denise Richards Divorce Battle Goes 'Nuclear'

author: Inside Edition
description: Vacationers on a wildlife expedition in Botswana came face to face with a charging elephant. The day started peacefully, as the tourists canoed through a swamp. They came upon a herd of elephants grazing, but they may have gotten too close. One elephant noticed them, and, believing her two calves were threatened, stormed towards them. The pachyderm turned over two of the canoes, and tried to stomp on one of the tourists.
title: Elephant Charges At American Tourists On Safari

author: Inside Edition
description: Social media is awash with Swifties of every age recreating moves from Taylor Swift's "The Fate of Ophelia" music video. One group even tried it on the New York City Subway. Inside Edition's Alison Hall visited Broadway Dance in New York City, where she learned the complicated choreography. It took some time, but finally she got the moves just right. Jimmy Fallon tried his hand at the fancy footwork on "The Tonight Show."
title: How To Do Taylor Swift's 'Dance of Ophelia' Moves

author: Inside Edition
description: A couple in Tennessee is apparently "on board" with Halloween, turning their home into a pirate ship! Bionner Puerta of Clarkesville tells WTVF he got the idea a few years ago when he dressed as Captain Jack Sparrow for Halloween. A trick-or-treater asked him, "where's your ship?" If that kid comes back, he won't have to ask, just look. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Retired Combat Vet Turns House Into Pirate Ship For Halloween

author: Inside Edition
description: Joyce D'Arcy wants to raise awareness after her husband suddenly died after coming in contact with a flesh-eating bacteria. The pair went to Virginia Beach, and Derek didn't feel good after coming home. He went to the hospital, and doctors discovered he had come in contact with Vibrio. He died 13 days later. Now Joyce wants people to know how common Vibrio is. "If you have a weakened immune system, stay clear of the water," she told Inside Edition Digital's Andrea Swindall.
title: Man Dies From Flesh-Eating Bacteria After Visiting Virginia Beach

author: Inside Edition
description: Circuit Court Judge Diane Goodstein of South Carolina was on a walk when her mansion went up in flames with her husband and son inside. They were injured as they escaped.
title: Did Arsonist Set Judge's House On Fire? #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Teenagers Pandora Kjolsrud and Evan Clark were found shot to death near a remote hiking trail in Arizona after a Memorial Day outing — and police say their accused killer called a police helpline saying he’d seen them.
title: Suspect Arrested In Murder Of Camping Arizona Teens #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: At the Minnesota Marine Art Museum, a painting depicting life at sea is just as expansive as an ocean. It also has a long title to go with it: "The Grand Panorama Of A Whaling Voyage 'Round The World."
title: This Painting Is Longer Than The Empire State Building Is Tall #shorts
